<br>
Actually it's a conjunction of &quot;you all&quot; as in:<br>
<br>
Do you all want to come with me?<br>
(as in ALL of the collective group of people and not just some)<br>
Do y'all want to come with me?<br>
<br>
While you is in and of itself a plural of itself, sometimes it is necessary to add the all to it when addressing a group of people so they know you mean the plural and not the singular.<br>
<br>
It's not really against grammar to say You all, and I don't <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>think</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> making a conjuction of it is either.  It's not the preferred form but it follows the rules of conjucted words  /shrug<br>
